The nucleus basalis of Meynert located in the substantia innominata (SI) of the basal forebrain provides the principal cholinergic input of the cortical areas and the pedunculopontine nucleus provides the major cholinergic input to the thalamus
In the present study, we hypothesized that cholinergic systems in the brain is related to the development of FOG and also influences cognitive performance in Parkinson’s disease.

Automatic analysis of subcortical structures revealed that thalamic volumes were significantly reduced in PD patients with FOG compared with those without FOG after adjusting for age, sex, disease duration, UPDRS score, BDI and total intracranial volume
